[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Approval[bold]3.1[bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Free Schools 
[normal]under
[normal]go a rigorous approval process,
[normal] distinct
[normal] from th
[normal]at for
[normal] both converter and sponsored academies
[normal]. 
[normal]Th
[normal]is
[normal] has evolved 
[normal]in every year since the programme began
[normal] and has built
[normal] on the experience of each 
[normal]of the five
[normal] 
[normal]application wave
[normal]s
[normal]. 
[normal]The tightening of this
[normal] process was
[normal] noted by the recent NAO report
[normal], which found that the DfE has, ‘incrementally improved its selection and pre-opening processes’.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.2[bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]current 
[normal]proc
[normal]ess 
[normal]is 
[normal]demanding
[normal], 
[normal]only 
[normal]26% of applications 
[normal]submitted 
[normal]have been approved by the DfE
[normal]. A
[normal] full s
[normal]ummary of each stage is included
[normal] as an a
[normal]ppendix but a
[normal] brief outline is provided
[normal] here.
[normal] 
[normal]At the application stage g
[normal]roups have to:
[normal]—
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Set out a strong vision for their school
[normal];
[normal]—
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Develop detailed education, finance and 
[normal]governance plans
[normal] 
[normal]and 
[normal]set out ambitious outcomes for their pupils
[normal];
[normal]—
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Prove they have the capacity and capability – especially in educational expertise – to run a 
[normal]good 
[normal]school
[normal];
[normal] and
[normal]—
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Prove there is need and demand for the school in their community.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.3[bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]This is not t
[normal]o say that further
[normal] improvements cannot be made to the current approvals process to make it more rigorous
[normal]. 
[normal]In particular NSN
[normal] believe
[normal]s
[normal] that greater expertise is needed when reviewing the governance elements of applications. With the growth of Multi-Academy Trusts (MATs) the complexity of governance arrangements is increasing and ensuring that groups 
[normal]have effective structures in place to 
[normal]govern new schools is critical.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.4[bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]The fast growth of the Free Schools programme
[normal] has also meant that the process
[normal] 
[normal]h
[normal]as
[normal] 
[normal]changed, often quite substantial
[normal]ly,
[normal] with each wave of applications. 
[normal]Having learned these lessons to create the more rigorous systems that are
[normal] in place today, it will now be important to maintain these standards consistently.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.5[bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Once groups 
[normal]are approved 
[normal]to open a Free School, they 
[normal]enter a ‘pre-opening’ phase during which they have to meet fur
[normal]ther stringent targets if
[normal] the school 
[normal]is 
[normal]to 
[normal]open. This 
[normal]includes developing comprehensive education plans and policies; building financial systems and recruiting pupils. They must also conduct a statutory consultation with the local community
[normal] while the DfE 
[normal]conducts an assessment of the impact the project will h
[normal]ave on other schools in the area.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.6[bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]The DfE provides oversight and challenge to the project through a series of che
[normal]ckpoint meetings and, 
[normal]before being allow
[normal]ed to open
[normal],
[normal] the school must 
[normal]be inspected by Ofsted to ensure premises 
[normal]and policies are up to standard
[normal].
[normal] If the school is found to be unsatisfactory at any stage then the 
[normal]project may be cancelled 
[normal]or delayed.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.7[bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Although L
[normal]ocal 
[normal]A
[normal]uthoritie
[normal]s have no formal role in the approval of Free Schools, NSN encourages all groups 
[normal]we work with 
[normal]to m
[normal]ake early contact with their
[normal] LA
[normal]. In many cases 
[normal]groups have been able to work collaboratively particularly
[normal] 
[normal]around
[normal] 
